{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"tsunamic-wax-hog","description":"## Context\n\nA documentation audit (final unified report, evaluated at commit `2272d68ca` =\n`origin/main`) surfaced front-door defects and factual drift in rebar's docs. Every\nfinding was re-validated against `origin/main` before filing this epic; one audit\nfinding (that `docs/config.md` mis-describes the config-file format) was **REFUTED**\n— the loader matches the doc exactly — and is deliberately excluded.\n\nOur audiences are human clients, LLM clients, human contributors, and LLM\ncontributors. The two highest-leverage moves are (a) fixing the immediate defects\nthat break onboarding/trust, and (b) adding cheap **drift-proofing** so the same\nclass of staleness cannot silently return — the true lever on maintenance burden.\n\n### Validated findings this epic remediates\n- P0: README `session-log` syntax is invalid (missing subcommand); README quickstart\n  is not actually one ticket end-to-end (hard-coded `reel-lot-tea`, separate Python\n  ticket, MCP shows config only).\n- P1: dependency count + `mcp` floor wrong in README and `docs/config.md` (truth: 3\n  base deps, `mcp>=1.9`); `docs/output-schemas.md` points at a moved source path and\n  describes a removed bash shell-out; stale bash-engine language in CI comments +\n  `leaf.py`.\n- P2: `docs/README.md` index is incomplete (4 unlinked living docs) and mixes living\n  references with historical evidence.\n\n### Reuse note (avoids duplicate work)\n- `scripts/probe-rebar.sh` already implements the full install→…→close golden path;\n  it just is not wired into CI.\n- `scripts/gen_env_registry.py` + its CI drift gate is a proven **generator +\n  drift-gate** pattern to template for new generated references.\n\n## Success Criteria\n- Every validated defect above is corrected against `origin/main`.\n- New CI gates make quickstart-command rot and docs-index drift fail the build\n  automatically (less manual doc upkeep).\n- The docs index is complete and clearly separates living reference from historical\n  evidence, with an intent-based router for the four audiences.\n- Volatile command/tool surfaces move toward generated references so they cannot go\n  stale by hand.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] All child tickets are closed (each with green CI / `Verified +1`).\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass on the aggregate.\n- [ ] The refuted config-format finding is NOT acted on (no spurious change).\n- [ ] Lower-value inventory work (Python-API / config-key) is captured as an `idea`,\n      not shipped speculatively.","id":"4191-b4f9-146a-43cd","parent_id":"","priority":1,"tags":["docs","remediation"],"ticket_type":"epic","title":"Documentation remediation: fix front-door defects, drift-proof the docs, clarify taxonomy"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783814556331170001,"uuid":"97a7594a-f28e-4ec0-a38c-e6af8d5decb5"}